For I being a finite indexing set, this coincides with Product of family of groups.

Let A, B, C be Groups. Let \mathbf {1} be the trivial group. A Short Exact Sequence describes
\mathbf {1}\to  A\xrightarrow {f} B\xrightarrow {g}C\to \mathbf {1}
where f\colon  A\to  B and g\colon  B\to  C are Group Morphisms such that \mathop {\textrm {Im}}\nolimits (f)=\ker (g).

