Let G and H be Groups. Let \widehat {G}_{1} and \widehat {G}_{2} be extensions of G by H. A Morphism of Extensions is a morphism \varphi \colon \widehat {G}_{1}\to \widehat {G}_{2} such that
\begin {array}{ccccccccc}
\mathbf {1} & \to  & H & \to  & \widehat {G}_{1} & \to  & G & \to  & \mathbf {1}\\
